{"case_id": "cpython-tcl-windows-matrix-v2-001", "context_method": "raw", "diagnoser": "real-agent-v1", "mode": "root_cause_diagnosis", "summary": "Two tests in test_tcl fail with AssertionError because Tcl eval returns surrogate pairs ('\\ud83d\\udcbb') instead of the expected combined Unicode character ('\\U0001f4bb'). The failures occur in both test_eval_surrogates_in_result and test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result, and persist on re-run.", "root_cause_category": "test_assertion", "root_cause": "The Tcl/Tkinter interface returns surrogate pair characters ('\\ud83d\\udcbb') instead of combining them into the proper Unicode code point ('\\U0001f4bb') when evaluating Tcl expressions containing surrogate-encoded emoji. Both test_eval_surrogates_in_result and test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result assert equality with the combined form but receive the surrogate pair form.", "confidence": 0.95, "relevant_files": ["D:\\a\\cpython\\cpython\\Lib\\test\\test_tcl.py"], "relevant_tests": ["test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_eval_surrogates_in_result", "test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result"], "evidence": [{"quote": "FAIL: test_eval_surrogates_in_result (test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_eval_surrogates_in_result)", "reason": "Identifies the first failing test in the test_tcl module"}, {"quote": "AssertionError: '<\\ud83d\\udcbb>' != '<ðŸ'»>'", "reason": "Shows the actual vs expected mismatch: surrogate pair returned instead of combined Unicode character"}, {"quote": "self.assertEqual(tcl.eval(r'set a \"<\\ud83d\\udcbb>\"'), '<\\U0001f4bb>')", "reason": "The test expects Tcl to combine the surrogate pair into a single Unicode code point U+1F4BB"}, {"quote": "FAIL: test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result (test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result)", "reason": "Identifies the second failing test with the same surrogate pair handling issue"}, {"quote": "test test_tcl failed (2 failures)", "reason": "Confirms both failures are in test_tcl and the test was re-run and failed again"}, {"quote": "1 test failed again:\n    test_tcl", "reason": "Confirms the failure is reproducible (not flaky) — test_tcl failed on re-run as well"}, {"quote": "patchlevel = 9.0.3", "reason": "Shows Tcl version 9.0.3 is being used, which may have different surrogate handling behavior"}], "suggested_fix": "Investigate the surrogate pair handling in the CPython Tcl/Tkinter C extension (_tkinter) for Tcl 9.0.3. The tests expect that surrogate pairs returned by Tcl are combined into proper Unicode code points, but the implementation is returning them as-is. Fix the string conversion logic in the _tkinter module to combine surrogate pairs (\\ud83d\\udcbb -> \\U0001f4bb) when decoding Tcl string results, or update the tests if Tcl 9.0.3 behavior is intentionally different.", "input": {"context_path": "results/v2/stress/raw/cpython-tcl-windows-matrix-v2-001.txt", "context_tokens_estimate": 142495}, "usage": {"processing_tokens_estimate": 0, "output_tokens_estimate": 1035}, "metadata": {"provider": "command", "prompt_sha256": "ecffdf03c99a91b0f8f75e086720d9fb8db96af0d9dae5285baf679c9c9d28de", "runtime_ms": 37612.953, "cache_key": "ea37a6efbeaf07e3249fca8744c564d1cb3ebf2eeecde12ac7e0f9a9527deefe", "provider_error": null, "provider_error_detail": null, "command": "python3 /Users/eyuansu62/llm_judge/cli-token-killer/cilog-bench/examples/diagnosis_shim_claude_agent.py", "model_info": {"provider_name": "anthropic", "requested_model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "resolved_model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "base_url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1", "usage": {"input_tokens": 47637, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1041, "service_tier": "standard", "inference_geo": "global"}}, "diagnoser_config_name": null, "diagnoser_config_sha256": "a87dd5e5ce51e6205be617b7a3c45c1647376786e44852f4b639352884f6c1ea", "shim_sha256": "9d926e0343b984d1ae4eacaf2f824d2bb26a2187