{"case_id": "nodejs-test-debugger-exec-timeout-v2-001", "context_method": "raw", "diagnoser": "real-agent-v1", "mode": "root_cause_diagnosis", "summary": "The test `parallel/test-debugger-exec` failed because the Node.js debugger client timed out (after 15000ms) waiting for the initial break message matching `/break (?:on start )?in/i`. The debugger attached successfully but never emitted the expected break-on-start line, causing the test to throw a Timeout error.", "root_cause_category": "test_assertion", "root_cause": "test-debugger-exec timed out waiting for the debugger to emit a 'break on start' message. The debugger attached and showed 'debug> ' prompt but never produced the expected break-in-script output, causing `waitForInitialBreak` to throw `Error: Timeout (15000) while waiting for /break (?:on start )?in/i`.", "confidence": 0.92, "relevant_files": ["test/parallel/test-debugger-exec.js", "test/common/debugger.js"], "relevant_tests": ["parallel/test-debugger-exec"], "evidence": [{"quote": "Error: Timeout (15000) while waiting for /break (?:on start )?in/i", "reason": "This is the exact error thrown by the test helper when the debugger did not emit the expected break-on-start message within 15 seconds."}, {"quote": "at Object.waitForInitialBreak (/Users/runner/work/node/node/node/test/common/debugger.js:116:18)", "reason": "The stack trace shows the timeout originated in waitForInitialBreak, confirming the debugger never signalled the initial break."}, {"quote": "output: '< Debugger listening on ws://127.0.0.1:49508/1fd32687-38b3-450e-96e5-4a28a88f601e\\n' +\n    '< For help, see: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/inspector\\n' +\n    '< \\n' +\n    'connecting to 127.0.0.1:49508 ...\\n' +\n    ' ok\\n' +\n    '< Debugger attached.\\n' +\n    '< \\n' +\n    '\\n' +\n    'debug> '", "reason": "The captured debugger output shows the debugger connected and attached, but the 'break in ...' line that the test expects was never printed, confirming the root cause."}, {"q